          </p>
          <p>
            We mix the resin and natural aggregate on site and trowel it to a consistent depth over a prepared asphalt or concrete base. The result is a uniform surface that doesn't ravel or loose stone. Available in a wide range of aggregate colours and blends, from warm natural tones to cooler slate greys — we can match your home's palette.
          </p>
          <p>
            Resin bound is particularly popular for modern outdoor entertaining spaces, around pools, and alongside contemporary home extensions across Tipperary. With minimal maintenance needed — a rinse and occasional brush is enough — it's one of the most fuss-free patio surfaces available.
          </p>
          <a href="/driveways-tipperary/" class="btn btn-outline-accent">Learn More About Resin</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Block 2: Natural Stone (reversed) -->
      <div class="service-block service-block--reversed">
        <div class="service-block__img">
          <img
            src="/assets/images/patios-stone.jpg"
            alt="Natural sandstone patio installation Tipperary"
            width="600"
            height="400"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="service-block__text">
          <span class="eyebrow">Natural Stone</span>
          <h3>Natural Stone Patios</h3>
          <span class="rule" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <p>
            There's a reason natural stone has been used in gardens for centuries — it ages beautifully, every slab is unique, and it suits everything from a traditional cottage garden to a sleek modern terrace. We work with sandstone, limestone, and slate, all carefully selected for colour consistency and durability.
          </p>
          <p>
            Natural stone requires a solid, well-prepared base and careful bedding to prevent movement and cracking over time. We use a full mortar bed technique rather than spot bedding, which gives a much more stable and long-lasting result. Joints are pointed with a suitable mortar mix that matches the stone and withstands frost.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you want a patio that looks better with age and adds genuine character to your outdoor space, natural stone is hard to beat. We'll help you choose the right type, thickness, and finish to suit your garden and budget.
          </p>
          <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-outline-accent">Get a Stone Patio Quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Block 3: Porcelain -->
      <div class="service-block">
        <div class="service-block__img">
          <img
            src="/assets/images/patios-porcelain.jpg"
            alt="Porcelain patio tiles laid in Tipperary garden"
            width="600"
            height="400"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="service-block__text">
          <span class="eyebrow">Porcelain</span>
          <h3>Porcelain Patio Tiles</h3>
          <span class="rule" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <p>
            Porcelain is the go-to surface for homeowners who want a high-end, ultra-low-maintenance patio with a sharp, contemporary edge. It's non-porous, frost-resistant, and virtually impossible to stain — which makes it perfect for outdoor dining areas and spaces that get heavy use.
          </p>
          <p>
            Laying porcelain correctly is a skilled job. The tiles are dense and heavy, cutting requires specialist equipment, and the base preparation must be absolutely level to prevent cracking. We use the correct adhesive mortars rated for outdoor porcelain and ensure every tile is fully bedded with no hollow spots beneath.
          </p>
          <p>
            Available in large format sizes and a huge range of finishes — concrete-effect, stone-effect, wood-effect — porcelain gives you the look you want without the upkeep. A rinse down with a hose is all it needs to stay looking brand new.
          </p>
          <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-outline-accent">Get a Porcelain Patio Quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Block 4: Block Paving (reversed) -->
      <div class="service-block service-block--reversed">
        <div class="service-block__img">
          <img
            src="/assets/images/patios-block.jpg"
            alt="Block paving patio installed in Tipperary"
            width="600"
            height="400"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="service-block__text">
          <span class="eyebrow">Block Paving</span>
          <h3>Block Paving Patios</h3>
          <span class="rule" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <p>
            Concrete block paving is one of the most versatile and cost-effective patio options available. Available in a wide range of colours, sizes, and laying patterns — herringbone, stretcher bond, basketweave — it can be tailored to suit both traditional and modern garden settings.
          </p>
          <p>
            Block paving is also one of the most practical choices for larger patio areas. Individual blocks can be lifted and relaid if underground access is ever needed, and the flexible jointing means it handles ground movement far better than rigid mortar-bedded surfaces. We install with a compacted sand-set base and kiln-dried jointing sand to lock everything in place.
          </p>
          <p>
            Whether you're extending an existing block paved driveway into a patio area or starting from scratch in the back garden, block paving delivers excellent value and longevity when laid properly — which is exactly how we do it.
          </p>
          <a href="/driveways-tipperary/" class="btn btn-outline-accent">See Our Driveway Work Too</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Block 5: Groundworks & Base Preparation -->
      <div class="service-block">
        <div class="service-block__img">
          <img
            src="/assets/images/patios-groundworks.jpg"
            alt="Patio sub-base groundworks preparation in Tipperary"
            width="600"
            height="400"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="service-block__text">
          <span class="eyebrow">Groundworks</span>
          <h3>Base Preparation & Groundworks</h3>
          <span class="rule" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <p>
            Every patio we build starts below the surface. Proper excavation, a correctly compacted MOT Type 1 sub-base, well-placed edging restraints, and a suitable bedding layer — these are the elements that determine whether your patio lasts five years or fifty. We never skip steps to save time, and we never use cheap fill material that will settle and shift.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our groundworks expertise also means we can handle complex site challenges — soft ground, high water tables, sloping sites, areas close to tree roots — that less experienced contractors might struggle with. We assess the ground conditions before we quote so there are no surprises mid-job.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you have existing drainage issues, we can address these as part of the patio build, installing channel drains, soakaways, or connecting new drain runs to your existing drainage system. Getting the water management right is just as important as the surface finish.
          </p>
          <a href="/services/" class="btn btn-outline-accent">All Our Services</a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

