  <section class="patios-pricing" aria-labelledby="pricing-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Pricing Guidance</span>
      <h2 id="pricing-heading" class="section-title">How Much Does a Patio Cost in Tipperary?</h2>
      <p class="section-body">
        Straightforward question — here's an honest answer. Patio costs vary quite a bit based on size, material, and how much ground preparation is involved. The figures below are typical market guidance ranges for County Tipperary; your actual quote may sit higher or lower depending on your specific site. We'll give you a detailed, itemised quote after a free site visit — no vague estimates.
      </p>
      <div class="pricing-grid">
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <div class="pricing-card__label">Entry Level</div>
          <div class="pricing-card__title">Block Paving</div>
          <div class="pricing-card__range">€60 – €90 / m²</div>
          <p>Concrete block paving is the most cost-effective patio option. Price varies by block type, colour range, and laying pattern chosen. Ideal for larger areas where budget matters.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <div class="pricing-card__label">Mid Range</div>
          <div class="pricing-card__title">Resin Bound</div>
          <div class="pricing-card__range">€70 – €110 / m²</div>
          <p>Resin bound pricing reflects the specialist materials and equipment involved. Size of the area has a significant impact — larger areas benefit from lower per-m² rates.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <div class="pricing-card__label">Mid Range</div>
          <div class="pricing-card__title">Natural Stone</div>
          <div class="pricing-card__range">€80 – €120 / m²</div>
          <p>Natural stone pricing depends heavily on the stone type selected (sandstone, limestone, slate) and the thickness required. Import costs and stone grade affect the final figure.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <div class="pricing-card__label">Premium</div>
          <div class="pricing-card__title">Porcelain</div>
          <div class="pricing-card__range">€90 – €140 / m²</div>
          <p>Porcelain commands a premium due to material cost, specialist cutting equipment, and the skill required to lay large format tiles correctly. The low maintenance payback is significant over time.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <div class="pricing-card__label">Add-On</div>
          <div class="pricing-card__title">Steps & Edging</div>
          <div class="pricing-card__range">Priced per project</div>
          <p>Steps, retaining edges, raised planters, and integrated drainage are priced individually based on materials and complexity. We include everything in your quote upfront.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pricing-card">
          <div class="pricing-card__label">Variable</div>
          <div class="pricing-card__title">Groundworks Prep</div>
          <div class="pricing-card__range">Included in quote</div>
          <p>All our prices include excavation and sub-base preparation. Difficult ground conditions, deeper excavations, or spoil removal off-site may incur additional cost — we'll flag this in your quote.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pricing-factors">
        <h3>What Affects the Final Price?</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Total surface area — larger patios benefit from lower per-m² rates</li>
          <li>Material choice — stone type, porcelain grade, aggregate blend</li>
          <li>Depth of excavation required and ground conditions on site</li>
          <li>Spoil removal — how much material needs to be taken off site</li>
          <li>Drainage requirements — channels, soakaways, pipe connections</li>
          <li>Steps, level changes, or retaining walls needed</li>
          <li>Access to the site — tight access increases labour time</li>
          <li>Existing structures to work around — walls, manholes, trees</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

