          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-a5" id="faq-q5">
            What preparation work is involved before laying a patio?
            <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-a5" role="region" aria-labelledby="faq-q5">
            Good groundworks are the foundation of a long-lasting patio. Our process typically involves excavating the existing surface to the correct depth, laying a compacted sub-base of MOT Type 1 stone, installing edging restraints, and then applying a suitable bedding layer before laying the chosen surface material. Skipping any of these steps is a common cause of patio failure — we never cut corners.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-a6" id="faq-q6">
            Can you install a patio on a sloped garden?
            <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-a6" role="region" aria-labelledby="faq-q6">
            Absolutely. We regularly work on sloped and uneven sites across Tipperary and surrounding areas. Depending on the gradient, we may need to incorporate steps, retaining edges, or level out sections using additional fill material. We'll assess this as part of your free quote and design a solution that works with your garden's natural shape.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-a7" id="faq-q7">
            Is resin bound a good option for a patio?
            <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-a7" role="region" aria-labelledby="faq-q7">
            Resin bound is an excellent choice for patios where you want a smooth, modern finish with excellent drainage. It's SUDS-compliant, weed-resistant, and available in a wide range of aggregate colours and sizes. It's particularly popular for contemporary gardens and outdoor entertaining areas. We can show you samples and advise on the best aggregate blend for your project.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-a8" id="faq-q8">
            How do I maintain a patio once it's installed?
            <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-a8" role="region" aria-labelledby="faq-q8">
            Maintenance requirements vary by material. Resin bound patios need very little upkeep — an occasional rinse or light brush is enough. Natural stone and porcelain patios benefit from a yearly clean and periodic re-sealing to prevent staining and weathering. Block paving may need jointing sand topped up over time. We'll give you material-specific aftercare advice at handover.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-a9" id="faq-q9">
            Do you handle drainage as part of a patio installation?
            <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-a9" role="region" aria-labelledby="faq-q9">
            Yes. Proper drainage is a critical part of every patio we build. We ensure the surface has the correct fall angle to channel water away from the property, and we can install linear channel drains or point drains where needed. Our groundworks expertise means we can handle even complex drainage scenarios.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-a10" id="faq-q10">
            Do you offer a guarantee on your patio work?
            <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-a10" role="region" aria-labelledby="faq-q10">
            We stand behind the quality of our workmanship. All our patio installations come with a workmanship guarantee and we use quality-assured materials from reputable suppliers. If anything isn't right, we'll come back and sort it — that's our commitment to every customer across Tipperary.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-a11" id="faq-q11">
            What areas in Tipperary do you cover for patio installations?
            <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-a11" role="region" aria-labelledby="faq-q11">
            We cover the full county of Tipperary including Tipperary Town, Clonmel, Nenagh, Thurles, Carrick-on-Suir, Cahir, Roscrea, Templemore, Cashel, and Newport, plus all surrounding townlands and rural areas. If you're unsure whether we cover your area, just give us a ring.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-a12" id="faq-q12">
            How do I get a quote for a patio in Tipperary?
            <svg class="faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-a12" role="region" aria-labelledby="faq-q12">
            Getting a quote is simple. Use the contact form on this page, drop us an email at <a href="mailto:tipperarygroundworks@gmail.com" style="color: var(--pd-accent);">tipperarygroundworks@gmail.com</a>, or call us directly on <a href="tel:+353873566934" style="color: var(--pd-accent);">+353 87 356 6934</a>. We'll arrange a no-obligation site visit at a time that suits you and provide a clear, itemised quote with no hidden costs.
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</div>

<script>
  (function () {
    var buttons = document.querySelectorAll('.tipperary-groundworks-patios .faq-question');
    buttons.forEach(function (btn) {
      btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
        var expanded = this.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true';
        var answerId = this.getAttribute('aria-controls');
        var answer = document.getElementById(answerId);
        buttons.forEach(function (b) {
          b.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
          var id = b.getAttribute('aria-controls');
          var a = document.getElementById(id);
          if (a) a.classList.remove('open');
        });
        if (!expanded) {
          this.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');
          if (answer) answer.classList.add('open');
        }
      });
    });
  })();
</script>

{% endblock %}